This paper discusses load balancing techniques in parallel computing systems, which involves distributing tasks among processing elements. This topic falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper involves performance analysis, which could fall under Performance (cs.PF) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses dynamic algorithms, which could fall under Software Engineering (cs.SE) or Programming Languages (cs.PL).
